<figureCitation box="[1242,1370,1938,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1784,1806]" captionTargetBox="[164,1412,714,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,697,1763]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Adult morphology of Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina. 13 – 16 in lateral view. 13, male palpus; 14, male foreleg; 15, male middle leg; 16, female foreleg; 17, forewing venation; 18, hind wing venation. Scale bars = 0.5 and 1.8 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Figs. 13–16</figureCitation>
